00:31.532 --> 00:35.419
"Wives, submit yourselves
to your husbands

00:35.544 --> 00:37.996
"as is fitting in the Lord.

00:38.162 --> 00:43.861
"Husbands, love your wives
and do not be harsh with them.

00:43.986 --> 00:48.256
"Children, obey your
parents in everything

00:48.422 --> 00:50.703
"for this pleases the Lord.

00:50.828 --> 00:54.440
"Slaves, obey your earthly
masters in everything,

00:54.565 --> 00:57.009
"not only when their eye is on you

00:57.134 --> 01:03.647
and to curry the favor,
but when sin... sin..."

01:03.813 --> 01:06.733
Sincerity.

01:06.899 --> 01:09.389
"Sincerity of the heart

01:09.514 --> 01:12.239
in referring to the Lord."

01:12.405 --> 01:15.230
Well, I don't believe it.

01:15.355 --> 01:16.868
How old are you, boy?

01:17.034 --> 01:18.870
I ain't but 9 years, sir.

01:19.036 --> 01:20.871
Pay up, gentlemen.

01:20.996 --> 01:23.625
It's dangerous, you know,
teaching them to read.

01:23.791 --> 01:27.612
That's true.
Nat Turner was taught to read.

01:27.737 --> 01:28.839
Nonsense.

01:29.005 --> 01:30.815
Let me show you.

01:30.940 --> 01:34.919
Boy, can you explain
to me the meaning

01:35.044 --> 01:37.454
of what you just read?

01:37.579 --> 01:38.980
No, master.

01:39.599 --> 01:40.357
See?

01:40.482 --> 01:43.103
It's like a parrot
reciting Shakespeare.

01:43.269 --> 01:47.649
Well done, Elam.
Well done.

02:25.130 --> 02:28.476
"Now, I have heard the
groaning of the Israelites

02:28.601 --> 02:31.613
"whom the Egyptians hold in slavery,

02:31.738 --> 02:33.570
"and I have remembered my promise.

02:34.070 --> 02:38.378
"Say unto the children of Israel,
I am the Lord."

02:40.868 --> 02:44.627
"And I will bring you out from
under the burdens of the Egyptians,

02:44.752 --> 02:47.834
and I will rid you out
from under their bondage."

02:48.000 --> 02:50.934
"And I will redeem you
with a stretched out arm,

02:51.059 --> 02:54.174
and ye shall know that
I am the Lord."

03:19.573 --> 03:22.911
